    <h3>Connections</h3>
        <p>Component video cables that are not connected properly between the source and the TV can produce pictures with wrong colors. Conventionally at both ends of the bundle the green connector connects to the Y jack, the red connector connects to the Pr jack, and the blue connector connects to the Pb jack. Keep in mind that the signals in these cables really don't care what the colors of the connectors are, as long as the proper signal from the source connects to the proper input at the other end.</p>
        <p>Cables can become intermittent or go bad at their connectors. This can happen when the cable is disconnected repeatedly by grabbing it by the cable itself and tugging, rather than grasping the connector to disconnect it. This same @ViewBag.Spell_practice can also damage the female connector on the TV (see Circuit Board below).</p>
